caption: I been to this location a few times but, Farabe and I stopped by here recently for some tacos to go. Upon entry, there was three men gathered to one side of the restaurant talking without using their masks. Indoor dining has not been approved at this time.  There was one person who took the order and another person who made the order.  None of them washed their hands or put on their mask while working. The third person was just consuming beer and talking without putting on a mask.  The cashier who took our order was rude and unfriendly. He seemed impatient while taking our order. Every time I been here, the customer service has subpar. T  The single paper menu they have is incorrect and doesn't have all the dishes listed.  I ordered three tacos and a side order of rice and beans. I got the pollo guisado, camaron, and pollo mole. I like that each taco had different flavors and taste. I noticed that some of the tacos had stuff in them that wasn't listed under their description.  I did find some of the ingredients a bit stale like the shrimp and the tortillas. The rice and beans was okay, I added a some hot sauce and it was better.

It was so big I almost didn’t finish it.... but then realized how ridiculous that would have been and quickly polished it off 😇😇 Very reasonably priced with a friendly staff and the open kitchen where you watch the guys fix your food. Limited seating but worth a trip regardless. I’ll definitely return!!

Clearly they are not in the business to do business if that’s how they operate. I will never eat here again.. I’d rather chew my fingers off if this was the last place on earth to eat. They’d still be late.
